# Accessibility Guidelines

## Implementation Requirements

Implement accessibility features on all interactive elements:

- Add `tabindex="0"` for keyboard navigation on non-standard interactive elements.
- Include `aria-label` attributes for screen readers.
- Implement both `onClick` and `onKeyDown` handlers for interactive elements.
- Use semantic HTML elements when possible (button, nav, main, etc.).

## Keyboard Interaction

- Ensure all interactive elements are keyboard accessible.
- Support Enter and Space keys for button-like interactions.
- Implement proper focus management and visible focus indicators.

## ARIA Attributes

- Use appropriate ARIA roles when semantic HTML is insufficient.
- Add descriptive labels for all form inputs and interactive elements.
- Implement ARIA states (aria-expanded, aria-hidden, etc.) where appropriate.
